1
00:00:28,803 --> 00:00:30,973
Hello, who is it?

2
00:00:30,973 --> 00:00:35,153
Hey Chiharu! I told you not to answer the phone, didn't I?

3
00:00:35,223 --> 00:00:38,273
It's Chiharu! Hello! Hello!

4
00:00:38,273 --> 00:00:40,733
Hello, you've reached the Shigeno residence.

5
00:00:42,563 --> 00:00:44,113
Goro nii-chan!

6
00:00:50,293 --> 00:00:50,467
Kyowa Institute University for Girls

7
00:00:50,293 --> 00:00:54,203
Kyowa Institute University for Girls

8
00:00:54,203 --> 00:00:59,463
Even given the current condition, when we take
the positive law from the ancient times...

9
00:01:00,713 --> 00:01:03,383
I have no idea of what he's talking about...

10
00:01:03,663 --> 00:01:05,673
I hope we'll finish a bit early.

11
00:01:07,173 --> 00:01:11,013
And there aren't any club activities today... I'm so bored.

12
00:01:11,013 --> 00:01:14,393
Really, is there anything you like besides softball?

13
00:01:14,393 --> 00:01:17,273
W-What's wrong with that?

14
00:01:17,273 --> 00:01:18,773
Nothing...

15
00:01:24,773 --> 00:01:29,533
Hmm, a text from Taiga? That's rare.

16
00:01:26,593 --> 00:01:30,493
{\an8}Note: From Taiga, Announcement for Big Sis! Seems like Shigeno returned. I'll let you know even though you are not interested in guys.

17
00:01:32,193 --> 00:01:32,300
Once Again

18
00:01:34,248 --> 00:01:36,668
Hey, Kaoru! What's up?

19
00:01:36,668 --> 00:01:39,668
Sorry! I'm skipping the next classes!

20
00:01:44,048 --> 00:01:46,838
Honda's back!

21
00:01:51,558 --> 00:01:56,688
Do your best! And don't you dare forget about
your promise about the first autograph!

22
00:01:57,938 --> 00:01:58,848
Yeah!

23
00:02:07,068 --> 00:02:10,698
Oh, crap! I forgot to put it in silent mode!

24
00:02:11,028 --> 00:02:12,778
Yes, hello?

25
00:02:12,778 --> 00:02:13,538
Taiga.

26
00:02:13,988 --> 00:02:16,748
Oh, it's you? What's up?

27
00:02:16,748 --> 00:02:22,168
Uh, about your text... Is it true that Honda's come back?

28
00:02:22,628 --> 00:02:24,628
Yeah, it's true.

29
00:02:25,338 --> 00:02:28,678
Apparently he called Professor Yamada
to tell him that he was back in Japan.

30
00:02:29,178 --> 00:02:30,798
Oh, I see...

31
00:02:30,798 --> 00:02:35,678
Anything else? Did you hear anything about his plans for now?

32
00:02:36,478 --> 00:02:41,938
Well, first, he said he will start doing his solo training again soon,
but he said he'll show his face at the baseball club first

33
00:02:41,938 --> 00:02:42,768
I see...

34
00:02:43,228 --> 00:02:48,148
What's wrong? If you're so interested in what he's
doing, why don't you go directly to his house?

35
00:02:49,568 --> 00:02:53,078
Well, you do want to see him don't you?
So why don't you go right now?

36
00:02:53,078 --> 00:02:54,408
T-That...

37
00:02:54,408 --> 00:02:56,118
Why don't you go and kiss him, huh?

38
00:02:57,038 --> 00:02:58,908
That's not it at all!

39
00:03:04,378 --> 00:03:10,428
Well, well, she's a bit too old to still be
playing the pure and innocent virgin...

40
00:03:10,428 --> 00:03:12,338
Note: Third from top is Shigeno Goro

41
00:03:17,268 --> 00:03:22,558
It's somewhat irritating, but I'll give it a try.

42
00:03:26,978 --> 00:03:28,278
<i>I wonder if he's here.</i>

43
00:03:32,528 --> 00:03:36,078
<i>Ah no, he just came home today...</i>

44
00:03:36,658 --> 00:03:40,248
<i>It's probably a good idea if I just let him be alone with his family.</i>

45
00:03:42,998 --> 00:03:45,208
<i>No, that's no good. I'd better just go home.</i>

46
00:03:45,708 --> 00:03:49,008
<i>Besides, why should I come and meet him?</i>

47
00:03:49,208 --> 00:03:50,758
Oh, it's you Shimizu!

48
00:03:52,048 --> 00:03:56,098
Ah, ma'am! I'm sorry I haven't contacted you for so long.

49
00:03:56,098 --> 00:03:59,808
It's been a while, yes... So how is it going at the University?

50
00:04:00,098 --> 00:04:07,318
Translator's Note: goukons are joint parties between two or more
groups belonging to different universities or companies.

51
00:04:00,098 --> 00:04:04,688
Uh... Yes, well... hm, well I'm really into the softball club and
also into goukon, and of course I don't have any boyfriends.

52
00:04:08,228 --> 00:04:10,938
I-I didn't need that many details, but...

53
00:04:16,118 --> 00:04:17,828
He's here you know. Goro.

54
00:04:18,908 --> 00:04:23,168
He's arrived this morning, so I think he's
still sleeping because of the jet lag.

55
00:04:23,168 --> 00:04:26,208
Oh, I see. Then I'll come another time--

56
00:04:26,208 --> 00:04:27,418
Can you wait a moment?

57
00:04:27,838 --> 00:04:31,758
I think I can get him out of bed and on his
feet if I tell him that you came to see him.

58
00:04:32,508 --> 00:04:34,338
Ah, no! Don't...

59
00:04:50,608 --> 00:04:52,238
That's strange...

60
00:04:52,238 --> 00:04:56,488
I'm sorry, it seems he left without leaving a note.

61
00:04:57,488 --> 00:04:59,078
I wonder where to...

62
00:04:59,078 --> 00:05:02,538
And since he just came back, he doesn't have a cell phone yet.

63
00:05:02,538 --> 00:05:04,538
I'm sorry you had to come for nothing.

64
00:05:04,538 --> 00:05:07,128
It's okay. I'll come again.

65
00:05:12,798 --> 00:05:15,878
<i>But where did he go?</i>

66
00:05:16,798 --> 00:05:21,718
<i>Maybe he went to see Tashiro or Fuji, or even Komori?</i>

67
00:05:21,718 --> 00:05:24,388
<i>Maybe he wanted to meet with Toshiya-kun now that he's a pro?</i>

68
00:05:26,518 --> 00:05:29,978
<i>In any case, he didn't come to see me.</i>

69
00:05:42,788 --> 00:05:44,618
<i>He's not here either.</i>

70
00:05:44,618 --> 00:05:51,208
Well, I suppose it was to be expected, now that
he's a pro, he wouldn't want to come here.

71
00:05:51,208 --> 00:05:53,548
Oh? Is that you, Shimizu?

72
00:05:55,668 --> 00:05:57,338
Komori!

73
00:06:00,798 --> 00:06:03,348
So Honda-kun's back, huh?

74
00:06:03,348 --> 00:06:07,518
Yeah, so I went right over to his place
to meet him, but he wasn't there.

75
00:06:08,348 --> 00:06:12,978
I want to see him, too. He's making
quite the triumphant return, huh?

76
00:06:12,978 --> 00:06:18,908
If he plays in the Majors next year, I'm
sure he'll become a star right away.

77
00:06:19,608 --> 00:06:24,698
Of course that makes me happy, but somehow I feel like
he's getting even bigger and slipping farther away.

78
00:06:27,828 --> 00:06:29,248
Well, then...

79
00:06:29,918 --> 00:06:33,798
Maybe I should go and challenge Gibson... As if...

80
00:06:33,798 --> 00:06:35,008
Oh, by the way,

81
00:06:35,508 --> 00:06:41,218
Shimizu, don't you think the first place Honda would
want to go as soon as he's back in Japan might be...

82
00:07:17,548 --> 00:07:19,468
Honda

83
00:07:23,348 --> 00:07:26,098
See you later dad, I'll come back.

84
00:07:38,988 --> 00:07:40,488
Shimizu!

85
00:07:42,158 --> 00:07:44,368
W-What a coincidence!

86
00:07:44,368 --> 00:07:47,868
Liar! What are you doing here?

87
00:07:47,868 --> 00:07:55,088
Uh... Well... Komori said you might be here and...

88
00:07:58,338 --> 00:08:04,888
Sorry, I realized it was not really polite to interrupt
you while you were paying respect to your father...

89
00:08:05,718 --> 00:08:11,098
Ugly? Well, you're not the most beautiful, but
you shouldn't say that about yourself!

90
00:08:11,098 --> 00:08:12,848
I didn't say that!

91
00:08:12,848 --> 00:08:16,518
Oh, uh... Then... It's all right.

92
00:08:16,518 --> 00:08:21,028
Well since you're here, come and meet my dad!

93
00:08:21,818 --> 00:08:24,528
Are you sure?

94
00:08:24,908 --> 00:08:28,198
Yeah, my dad will like that.

95
00:08:28,198 --> 00:08:30,118
Honda Family

96
00:08:37,588 --> 00:08:39,168
So, are you all right?

97
00:08:40,208 --> 00:08:44,588
I've been following your performance on
the internet and sports magazines.

98
00:08:45,178 --> 00:08:48,048
It looks like you'll be promoted to the Majors next year, right?

99
00:08:48,048 --> 00:08:49,718
Who knows.

100
00:08:50,098 --> 00:08:55,558
The front office guys at the Hornets decided to
postpone my promotion when they heard about how,

101
00:08:55,558 --> 00:08:58,568
I prioritized the Minors championship by pretending to be injured.

102
00:08:59,188 --> 00:09:05,268
So instead, before going to the Majors, I was asked
to participate in the Arizona Fall Season League.

103
00:09:07,488 --> 00:09:10,998
I think I got their attention now...

104
00:09:14,498 --> 00:09:17,708
Somehow I feel like he's getting even
bigger and slipping farther away.

105
00:09:20,378 --> 00:09:21,798
Oh, right!

106
00:09:22,548 --> 00:09:26,178
On my way back, I wanted to come by your place to give you this!

107
00:09:31,558 --> 00:09:34,978
I couldn't think of a really tasteful souvenir to bring you.

108
00:09:34,978 --> 00:09:38,858
That's the ball from the game where
I go my first save with the Bats.

109
00:09:39,228 --> 00:09:44,818
You said you'd like my autograph last summer's festival, right? So...

110
00:09:51,328 --> 00:09:52,408
Thank you.

111
00:09:55,338 --> 00:09:58,168
Wonder how fast I'll get a premium on it?

112
00:09:59,088 --> 00:10:01,418
You want to sell it!?

113
00:10:02,175 --> 00:10:05,055
Ah, what a feast that was!

114
00:10:05,055 --> 00:10:07,885
Man, that was good!

115
00:10:07,885 --> 00:10:12,515
Especially after eating hamburgers and sandwiches
almost every day over there.

116
00:10:12,515 --> 00:10:15,435
Nothing compares to Japanese meals!

117
00:10:15,435 --> 00:10:19,145
What you mean of course is "nothing compares
to your Mom's Japanese meals", right?

118
00:10:20,315 --> 00:10:25,825
Yes that's it. Hey, Shingo, don't leave the tomatoes Mom made you!

119
00:10:25,825 --> 00:10:27,035
She just cut them!

120
00:10:27,615 --> 00:10:29,455
Oh, you're back Goro!

121
00:10:29,785 --> 00:10:30,915
You look healthy!

122
00:10:30,915 --> 00:10:32,375
Pa-Papa!

123
00:10:32,375 --> 00:10:32,875
Papa!

124
00:10:34,375 --> 00:10:35,795
You're hanging in there.

125
00:10:36,245 --> 00:10:39,245
I never thought you would progress this much in just one year...

126
00:10:40,355 --> 00:10:41,755
Well, I was lucky...

127
00:10:42,215 --> 00:10:44,175
And next year, the Majors at last!

128
00:10:44,285 --> 00:10:49,175
Yeah, I'm starting to see Gibson's back now.

129
00:10:52,765 --> 00:10:54,305
Oh yeah, Father...

130
00:10:54,765 --> 00:10:57,315
Who won the Championship this year?

131
00:10:58,105 --> 00:11:00,975
Did Toshiya or Mayumura become regulars?

132
00:11:01,315 --> 00:11:04,065
What? You mean you don't know?

133
00:11:05,405 --> 00:11:12,365
This year, I didn't have much time to pay attention
to the Japanese baseball news...

134
00:11:14,035 --> 00:11:14,995
I see.

135
00:11:14,995 --> 00:11:18,585
You can take a look at the details yourself, on the computer.

136
00:11:18,585 --> 00:11:21,295
Uh? On the computer?

137
00:11:22,255 --> 00:11:25,135
What, don't tell me you can't use one?

138
00:11:26,045 --> 00:11:27,215
What's wrong with that?

139
00:11:27,805 --> 00:11:28,675
Shingo.

140
00:11:29,175 --> 00:11:31,765
Why don't you show your brother how to use the computer?

141
00:11:31,765 --> 00:11:33,135
No problem.

142
00:11:33,685 --> 00:11:35,015
Thanks.

143
00:11:35,015 --> 00:11:36,545
Come on, Goro nii-chan!

144
00:11:37,815 --> 00:11:39,275
Me, too!

145
00:11:39,275 --> 00:11:41,235
Okay, Chiharu you're coming too!

146
00:11:47,025 --> 00:11:48,815
So he didn't have the time, huh?

147
00:11:49,235 --> 00:11:51,785
No wonder he performed that well.

148
00:11:52,905 --> 00:11:56,655
So you just have to input the word you want to look up here.

149
00:11:57,085 --> 00:12:01,155
Wow, that's great! You're a genius, aren't you?

150
00:12:01,585 --> 00:12:03,585
It's just common sense!

151
00:12:04,425 --> 00:12:06,335
Chiharu, let's go downstairs to play.

152
00:12:07,175 --> 00:12:08,255
What about Goro nii-chan?

153
00:12:08,595 --> 00:12:09,675
Oh!

154
00:12:08,675 --> 00:12:09,675
Later!

155
00:12:09,675 --> 00:12:12,335
The first victory for the Tokyo Warriors in two years?

156
00:12:13,725 --> 00:12:16,765
So the Oceans are in last place or something? That's lame!

157
00:12:18,305 --> 00:12:22,305
Mayumura, with an ERA of 2.78 is in the top five of the whole league!

158
00:12:22,605 --> 00:12:25,945
With 11 wins and 8 losses, he's the best of Yokohama!

159
00:12:25,945 --> 00:12:28,305
Which means he got the Rookie of the Year title?

160
00:12:29,115 --> 00:12:32,155
Well, that's not that surprising, I suppose.

161
00:12:33,445 --> 00:12:34,315
What!?

162
00:12:34,995 --> 00:12:38,285
"At the plate, he has a batting average of .312 with 18 home runs.

163
00:12:38,285 --> 00:12:42,335
In defense, after he became the starter last June
because Yatabe withdrew due to an injury,

164
00:12:42,795 --> 00:12:47,335
he's been performing extraordinarily, pulling the team with
incredible strength toward a tremendous turnaround."

165
00:12:50,005 --> 00:12:54,055
Amazing Toshi! No, Mayumura, too!

166
00:12:54,475 --> 00:12:57,805
Wow, I'm so happy!

167
00:13:07,655 --> 00:13:09,155
Hey, Sato...

168
00:13:10,185 --> 00:13:12,825
There's a journalist waiting for an interview in the lobby.

169
00:13:13,535 --> 00:13:15,955
Oh, all right, excuse me.

170
00:13:17,365 --> 00:13:19,285
Uh... Sorry for making you wait.

171
00:13:19,285 --> 00:13:23,705
Oh, it's no problem really, it's my fault for imposing
this interview on you without an appointment.

172
00:13:24,255 --> 00:13:28,995
And after you won the Rookie of the Year award, I thought it would
have gone to your head, and I would be turned away at the door.

173
00:13:30,175 --> 00:13:31,925
Hmm, Toshi?

174
00:13:32,455 --> 00:13:34,965
Have you already forgotten my voice?

175
00:13:35,975 --> 00:13:37,595
Goro!

176
00:13:39,805 --> 00:13:44,675
And that's how I thought I'd come to tell you I was back, and
at the same time see the face of the new Rookie of the Year.

177
00:13:44,935 --> 00:13:46,985
I see. I'm grateful.

178
00:13:46,985 --> 00:13:49,445
Oh, by the way, I got you a little souvenir from the States.

179
00:13:49,445 --> 00:13:51,655
<i>No, those are clearly Japanese sweets...</i>

180
00:13:51,655 --> 00:13:57,575
But, you are amazing, too. I was checking up
on your performance through the internet.

181
00:13:58,035 --> 00:14:00,035
It's just starting now really.

182
00:14:00,035 --> 00:14:02,875
I don't have any guarantee that I'll be promoted to the Majors,

183
00:14:02,875 --> 00:14:07,295
and even if I do, I don't think it'll be easy to stay on the main roster.

184
00:14:07,295 --> 00:14:08,795
<i>He's even eating them.</i>

185
00:14:09,335 --> 00:14:12,135
W-Well, that's true for me, too.

186
00:14:12,135 --> 00:14:15,795
Next year, Yatabe, the starting catcher,
will come back after he's recovered.

187
00:14:16,135 --> 00:14:18,545
The real competition to be a starter will start then.

188
00:14:19,055 --> 00:14:24,965
But to be honest, with the good results I got, I was hoping I might
get selected as a member of the Japanese national team.

189
00:14:25,925 --> 00:14:28,565
The Japanese national team? What's that?

190
00:14:28,565 --> 00:14:30,815
Eh, you don't know?

191
00:14:30,815 --> 00:14:31,525
What is it?

192
00:14:32,115 --> 00:14:35,865
Next spring, the Baseball World Cup
tournament composed of sixteen countries,

193
00:14:35,865 --> 00:14:40,915
will be held in the USA to determine
who's really the best team in the world.

194
00:14:42,125 --> 00:14:45,415
What? A tournament to determine the
best baseball team in the world?

195
00:14:45,415 --> 00:14:49,295
That's right. The members of the delegation
were officially announced yesterday.

196
00:14:49,875 --> 00:14:56,095
Coming from the Majors and the top Japanese players, they
all deserve the honor of being a representative, really.

197
00:14:56,635 --> 00:14:59,345
The only rookie selected was Mayumura.

198
00:14:59,885 --> 00:15:01,345
Mayumura?

199
00:15:01,805 --> 00:15:04,605
I wanted to be selected, too... But, I wasn't.

200
00:15:06,765 --> 00:15:09,815
The American national team was announced, too.

201
00:15:10,235 --> 00:15:13,695
It started with Gibson and then a list of first-class Major Leaguers

202
00:15:14,905 --> 00:15:16,115
Gibson!?

203
00:15:20,965 --> 00:15:24,445
It's a dream tournament that gathers
all the top players in the world.

204
00:15:25,035 --> 00:15:28,245
How exciting would it have been to
be selected for the Japanese team?

205
00:15:30,715 --> 00:15:32,535
<i>The Japanese national team?</i>

206
00:15:33,175 --> 00:15:37,045
<i>It doesn't really concern me for now.</i>

207
00:15:37,045 --> 00:15:39,045
Softball Club

208
00:15:37,215 --> 00:15:37,965
I'm off

209
00:15:37,965 --> 00:15:38,885
Thank you for today!

210
00:15:38,885 --> 00:15:39,465
Bye!

211
00:15:39,465 --> 00:15:41,215
I'm so sorry, Shimi!

212
00:15:41,975 --> 00:15:46,105
My boyfriend caught a cold and now we have
no way of going to that concert tonight.

213
00:15:46,895 --> 00:15:49,775
Wasn't it Asami who invited you in the first place?

214
00:15:49,795 --> 00:15:50,525
Yeah, and I'm greatful but...

215
00:15:51,105 --> 00:15:55,055
I'm giving you my tickets so you can go with somebody else.

216
00:15:55,905 --> 00:15:56,655
What?

217
00:15:56,655 --> 00:15:58,405
With someone? But in such short notice--

218
00:15:58,405 --> 00:15:59,615
Sorry...

219
00:16:02,365 --> 00:16:03,245
A concert?

220
00:16:03,525 --> 00:16:06,955
Yes, you like this band, right?

221
00:16:06,955 --> 00:16:10,245
That's no good. We have our final exams starting next week.

222
00:16:10,575 --> 00:16:13,295
That's why I'm here studying instead of going to practice.

223
00:16:13,835 --> 00:16:15,675
Just as I thought, it's not possible.

224
00:16:15,675 --> 00:16:20,675
Maki and Misaki couldn't go either, even though
I would have been happy going with anyone.

225
00:16:20,675 --> 00:16:22,765
Did you ask Shigeno senpai?

226
00:16:23,715 --> 00:16:26,345
After all, he probably has a lot of free time, right?

227
00:16:26,345 --> 00:16:33,485
Why would I ask him? There's just no way he would go
to a concert, you know he's only interested in baseball!

228
00:16:35,195 --> 00:16:37,195
You're afraid he'll say no.

229
00:16:38,115 --> 00:16:45,035
Not that I really care about your love life, but I'm sure you're
frustrated enough since you've become a university student.

230
00:16:45,495 --> 00:16:48,325
But I can't see why you can't take it easy
and invite him to a simple concert.

231
00:16:48,325 --> 00:16:54,715
I'm telling you he's just not interested! I don't want to bother
him with this invitation just because we're childhood friends--

232
00:16:54,715 --> 00:16:57,795
So, you're content to always be just childhood friends?

233
00:17:00,135 --> 00:17:05,175
If he's refusing to go to a simple concert with you, it's not because
he's not interested in the music, but that he's not interested in you.

234
00:17:06,135 --> 00:17:09,795
If there's no spark, maybe you should try and
direct your efforts towards someone else.

235
00:17:16,815 --> 00:17:18,445
Goro, can you answer?

236
00:17:18,855 --> 00:17:20,025
All right!

237
00:17:21,985 --> 00:17:23,235
Hello?

238
00:17:23,785 --> 00:17:25,745
Oh, it's you, Shimizu?

239
00:17:26,285 --> 00:17:27,865
Oh, a concert?

240
00:17:27,865 --> 00:17:31,165
What, nobody else wants to go?

241
00:17:31,165 --> 00:17:32,875
As I thought, it's not your thing.

242
00:17:34,255 --> 00:17:35,965
If you can't go, just tell me--

243
00:17:35,965 --> 00:17:36,465
Sounds good.

244
00:17:38,925 --> 00:17:41,385
They open the door for ticket holders at six, right?

245
00:17:45,015 --> 00:17:47,175
Was that Shimizu?

246
00:17:47,175 --> 00:17:52,145
Yeah, apparently she suddenly found herself with no
one to go to a concert, so she's asked me if I could.

247
00:17:53,065 --> 00:17:55,315
Since I'm free anyway, I said I would go.

248
00:18:03,365 --> 00:18:06,445
Ah, what am I going to do?! What am I going to wear?!

249
00:18:06,445 --> 00:18:08,655
Uh, this isn't good. Uh...

250
00:18:10,325 --> 00:18:11,375
Hey!

251
00:18:12,455 --> 00:18:13,705
I'm home!

252
00:18:14,245 --> 00:18:15,705
Welcome back!

253
00:18:21,005 --> 00:18:23,285
Hey Goro, are you going somewhere?

254
00:18:23,715 --> 00:18:25,425
Yeah.

255
00:18:27,515 --> 00:18:29,685
He has a date with Shimizu!

256
00:18:31,055 --> 00:18:32,475
It's not what you think!

257
00:18:33,075 --> 00:18:34,465
You're here early today.

258
00:18:34,785 --> 00:18:38,705
Yeah, we've finished this years adjustment for the World Cup, so...

259
00:18:39,635 --> 00:18:41,205
Adjustments for the World Cup?

260
00:18:41,205 --> 00:18:44,125
Father, are you working for the World Cup?

261
00:18:45,115 --> 00:18:45,765
Yeah.

262
00:18:46,085 --> 00:18:49,005
I'm the pitching and head coach for the national team.

263
00:18:49,555 --> 00:18:50,675
I didn't tell you?

264
00:18:52,055 --> 00:18:53,935
No, you didn't!

265
00:18:53,935 --> 00:18:58,605
Then why couldn't you get me or Toshi selected, father?

266
00:18:58,865 --> 00:19:00,995
Hey, don't talk nonsense.

267
00:19:01,145 --> 00:19:04,275
The right to decide who's selected belongs to Coach Sasaki anyway.

268
00:19:04,945 --> 00:19:07,065
Besides you're just a Minor Leaguer,

269
00:19:07,065 --> 00:19:10,195
and as for Sato, the burden of being the catcher
for that team is still a bit too heavy.

270
00:19:10,785 --> 00:19:12,655
Of course, it's not impossible.

271
00:19:14,535 --> 00:19:16,035
There's no rush, you know.

272
00:19:16,035 --> 00:19:19,245
You're still very young, you'll have your chance.

273
00:19:19,915 --> 00:19:22,505
There will be another World Cup in four years.

274
00:19:23,045 --> 00:19:24,715
In four years, huh?

275
00:19:25,295 --> 00:19:31,305
So this is the last time one could fight against
the American team with Gibson on it.

276
00:19:38,185 --> 00:19:38,865
Goro!

277
00:19:39,225 --> 00:19:43,605
Although the odds aren't very high, there's
still a way to be selected for the team.

278
00:19:44,935 --> 00:19:48,605
There will be a practice game during training
camp for the national team next January.

279
00:19:48,605 --> 00:19:52,235
They plan to pick up some of the young pro players who
will play against the delegation during that match.

280
00:19:52,785 --> 00:19:56,155
If you manage to catch Coach Sasaki's
eye with your skills during the game,

281
00:19:56,155 --> 00:19:58,865
then there's a slight chance you might be selected.

282
00:19:59,875 --> 00:20:06,165
And this is because he's a coach who doesn't care about
careers or names, he only wants to bring the best of Japan.

283
00:20:08,175 --> 00:20:09,965
Mifune Station

284
00:20:08,175 --> 00:20:09,965
South Exit

285
00:20:16,425 --> 00:20:18,805
What, there's still a chance to get onto the national team?

286
00:20:18,805 --> 00:20:23,855
Yeah, during that practice match we just have to
perform well enough to appeal to the coach.

287
00:20:23,855 --> 00:20:30,105
And even if we don't get selected, just the chance to face
the best team in history is just too exciting, isn't it?

288
00:20:32,615 --> 00:20:34,035
What's wrong?

289
00:20:34,035 --> 00:20:37,405
Nothing, I was just thinking that you really haven't changed a bit.

290
00:20:38,405 --> 00:20:42,995
I'm in, that sort of chance is too good to pass on. I'll apply, too.

291
00:20:43,705 --> 00:20:46,375
Amd who knows we might be able to form a battery again.

292
00:20:47,505 --> 00:20:48,585
Father!

293
00:20:49,335 --> 00:20:51,965
Toshi said he'd apply to play on the practice game team as well!

294
00:20:51,965 --> 00:20:53,045
Oh, good.

295
00:20:53,425 --> 00:20:56,095
With that, I'm sure we'll be the first battery.

296
00:20:56,095 --> 00:20:57,675
Hey, Goro!

297
00:20:58,095 --> 00:20:59,685
Why are you still here?

298
00:21:00,435 --> 00:21:01,685
What do you mean "huh"?

299
00:21:02,145 --> 00:21:05,105
Weren't you supposed to meet Shimizu at six?

300
00:21:05,355 --> 00:21:07,855
Shimizu? Meeting?

301
00:21:10,525 --> 00:21:12,735
I completely forgot!

302
00:21:12,735 --> 00:21:14,615
Goro, call her first!

303
00:21:16,785 --> 00:21:18,445
It's probably her.

304
00:21:20,955 --> 00:21:23,325
Hello?

305
00:21:23,635 --> 00:21:26,165
Oh, Shimizu, I'm so sorry.

306
00:21:26,165 --> 00:21:29,755
Something came up and I lost track
of time. I was just about to leave.

307
00:21:30,185 --> 00:21:34,845
Oh, I see, you didn't call and I thought maybe
you had an accident or something...

308
00:21:35,095 --> 00:21:37,425
So you just haven't left yet!

309
00:21:38,095 --> 00:21:43,235
I'm sorry! But now that I think of it, if you wait for me
to arrive you'll just miss everything, won't you?

310
00:21:43,485 --> 00:21:47,395
Don't worry about me and just go by
yourself. I'm not worth the trouble.

311
00:21:55,695 --> 00:21:56,905
I understand.

312
00:21:57,575 --> 00:22:01,535
It's my fault, I shouldn't have invited
you on such short notice. I'm sorry.

313
00:22:07,475 --> 00:22:09,625
What, you're not going?

314
00:22:09,625 --> 00:22:11,795
Well yeah, if I leave now I won't make it.

315
00:22:12,055 --> 00:22:15,005
She shouldn't miss the concert just because
she has to wait for me, right?

316
00:22:30,990 --> 00:22:33,030
Taiga, dinner!

317
00:22:33,030 --> 00:22:34,160
All right.

318
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:40,790
Huh?

319
00:22:42,040 --> 00:22:46,920
What happened sis? It's not even eight
o'clock, what happened with the concert?

320
00:22:51,260 --> 00:22:56,560
You were wrong... It was a mistake to ask a guy like him.

321
00:22:56,970 --> 00:23:00,770
What's wrong? Didn't you go to the concert together?

322
00:23:00,770 --> 00:23:02,270
Did you guys have a fight--

323
00:23:02,270 --> 00:23:03,060
It's gone.

324
00:23:04,100 --> 00:23:05,800
Somehow all the excitement's gone.

325
00:23:06,070 --> 00:23:08,570
It's fine, nothing wrong with staying childhood friends forever.

326
00:23:11,073 --> 00:23:12,113
Cheers.

327
00:23:12,493 --> 00:23:17,573
Oh, Nogoro! It's been a while, how are you?

328
00:23:17,573 --> 00:23:18,993
Well, I'm good.

329
00:23:19,533 --> 00:23:22,873
I'm here about that phone call the other day.

330
00:23:22,873 --> 00:23:26,043
I was thinking about using the field to keep in shape.

331
00:23:26,043 --> 00:23:27,923
Oh yes, of course. That's not a problem.

332
00:23:28,583 --> 00:23:31,003
Besides, there aren't any practices now due to exams.

333
00:23:31,503 --> 00:23:32,423
Thanks!

334
00:23:32,423 --> 00:23:33,713
Ah Nogoro...

335
00:23:34,883 --> 00:23:37,433
While you're at it, could you go and talk to Shimizu?

336
00:23:37,433 --> 00:23:39,643
I'm sure he'd like to talk to his successful upperclassmen.

337
00:23:41,563 --> 00:23:43,903
I'm not sure he'd really like that.

338
00:23:46,393 --> 00:23:49,113
Heh, this brings back good memories;

339
00:23:49,313 --> 00:23:52,823
this field left us badly drained, but we were able to overcome it.

340
00:23:53,193 --> 00:23:56,543
And now you got some more new members.
I hear you're working hard, Captain.

341
00:23:56,823 --> 00:23:59,453
What sorts of results did you get over the summer?

342
00:23:59,453 --> 00:24:02,243
Nothing to speak of really. Clearly we're far from it.

343
00:24:02,743 --> 00:24:06,173
Actually, the only time Seishuu had results
was when you were on the team.

344
00:24:06,503 --> 00:24:09,713
Now, just getting beyond the second round is reason to be greatful.

345
00:24:14,213 --> 00:24:15,213
Senpai.

346
00:24:15,843 --> 00:24:16,553
Yeah?

347
00:24:16,553 --> 00:24:18,883
Did you do something to my sister yesterday?

348
00:24:20,723 --> 00:24:21,443
Huh?

349
00:24:21,603 --> 00:24:25,023
She came back home without going to the concert.

350
00:24:25,023 --> 00:24:25,563
Eh?

351
00:24:25,563 --> 00:24:28,193
And she was really angry for some reason.

352
00:24:28,193 --> 00:24:30,483
So I thought maybe you did something a little too abrupt or--

353
00:24:30,483 --> 00:24:32,363
Are you insane?!

354
00:24:32,693 --> 00:24:35,323
Then why was she so angry when she came back?

355
00:24:35,533 --> 00:24:37,663
Huh, what are you talking about?

356
00:24:38,113 --> 00:24:43,373
Something came up right before the start of the concert and
since I couldn't make it on time, I told her to go without me!

357
00:24:46,453 --> 00:24:48,253
Man, you're the worst.

358
00:24:48,253 --> 00:24:48,963
What?

359
00:24:48,963 --> 00:24:52,383
So you were going to be late, but why didn't you still go?

360
00:24:52,673 --> 00:24:55,173
You can always get in even when the concert has already begun,

361
00:24:55,503 --> 00:24:57,553
but that was beside the point, wasn't it?

362
00:24:58,383 --> 00:25:00,933
Point? What point are you talking about?

363
00:25:01,223 --> 00:25:04,353
She bought tickets because she wanted to see the concert, right?

364
00:25:04,353 --> 00:25:07,603
I was feeling bad about her missing half of it just
because of me, so I did what I did because,

365
00:25:07,603 --> 00:25:09,313
I thought that was the considerate thing to do!

366
00:25:09,613 --> 00:25:12,403
You really don't get it, do you?

367
00:25:14,823 --> 00:25:17,783
Excuse me, my class is about to start.

368
00:25:17,783 --> 00:25:19,363
Hey Taiga!

369
00:25:19,743 --> 00:25:21,793
What don't I understand?

370
00:25:22,573 --> 00:25:26,043
If you're that thick-headed, she'll be disgusted with you.

371
00:25:26,703 --> 00:25:31,043
I suppose it's fine if you have no intention
of ever having anything more than just...

372
00:25:31,043 --> 00:25:33,423
A childhood friendship relationship with my sister.

373
00:25:37,392 --> 00:25:38,842
Really?

374
00:25:38,842 --> 00:25:41,892
Yes, Coach Sasaki of the Japanese National Team insisted,

375
00:25:42,142 --> 00:25:47,932
that you were to be one of the players
selected for the Young Japan team.

376
00:25:48,732 --> 00:25:51,902
Thank you very much! Do you know about the others?

377
00:25:52,652 --> 00:25:57,282
Do you know if Shigeno Goro has been selected as a member?

378
00:25:57,282 --> 00:25:58,322
Shigeno?

379
00:25:58,322 --> 00:26:03,372
Y-Yes, right now he's the pitcher for the Memphis Bats in Triple A.

380
00:26:03,372 --> 00:26:07,202
Ah I see, I don't think he'll be able to make it.

381
00:26:12,338 --> 00:26:15,758
If you're that thick-headed, she'll be disgusted with you.

382
00:26:17,878 --> 00:26:22,218
I suppose it's fine if you have no intention
of ever having anything more than just...

383
00:26:22,468 --> 00:26:24,178
A childhood friendship relationship with my sister.

384
00:26:35,648 --> 00:26:38,488
It's too early to go home.

385
00:26:43,448 --> 00:26:44,988
Keep it coming; next one!

386
00:26:49,668 --> 00:26:50,578
Oops, sorry!

387
00:26:57,048 --> 00:26:58,258
More!

388
00:26:58,628 --> 00:27:02,388
It's getting dark, it's time we pack it up.

389
00:27:03,178 --> 00:27:04,308
Y-Yeah.

390
00:27:05,638 --> 00:27:07,058
I wonder what happened.

391
00:27:07,058 --> 00:27:11,978
The way she's losing herself completely in her training
seems like she's trying to get something off her mind.

392
00:27:11,978 --> 00:27:12,648
Yeah.

393
00:27:16,938 --> 00:27:18,988
<i>Sports sure are comforting.</i>

394
00:27:18,988 --> 00:27:20,568
<i>I feel a lot better.</i>

395
00:27:21,658 --> 00:27:22,908
<i>I'm over it anyway.</i>

396
00:27:23,738 --> 00:27:26,658
<i>Throwing myself into softball suits me well.</i>

397
00:27:28,068 --> 00:27:29,618
A peeping tom!

398
00:27:29,618 --> 00:27:32,878
I'm telling you I'm not a peeping tom, so stop shouting!

399
00:27:33,078 --> 00:27:35,728
Then explain to me what a man is doing here?

400
00:27:35,838 --> 00:27:39,548
Don't you know boys aren't allowed on campus?

401
00:27:39,548 --> 00:27:41,198
I didn't know!

402
00:27:41,218 --> 00:27:43,778
If you don't leave immediately, I'll call the guards.

403
00:27:43,928 --> 00:27:47,348
Will you just shut up! Do you have a
freshman by the name of Shimizu here?

404
00:27:47,678 --> 00:27:49,398
I just came to see her!

405
00:27:49,728 --> 00:27:51,388
Hu, Shimi?

406
00:27:53,478 --> 00:27:54,978
Hey, Shimizu!

407
00:27:55,358 --> 00:27:57,898
They're treating me like I'm some peeping tom...

408
00:27:58,148 --> 00:27:59,938
Please help me out!

409
00:28:01,318 --> 00:28:04,288
Say, is he the so-called boyfriend everyone is talking about?

410
00:28:04,488 --> 00:28:07,788
But that's no good, you know boys aren't allowed inside the school.

411
00:28:09,498 --> 00:28:12,708
Huh, who is this person?

412
00:28:13,498 --> 00:28:19,548
How could a softball girl as zealous as me have a boyfriend anyway?

413
00:28:21,218 --> 00:28:22,928
Call the guards, quick!

414
00:28:22,928 --> 00:28:23,428
Yes!

415
00:28:24,468 --> 00:28:27,308
Hey! Wait a second, I'm innocent!

416
00:28:27,548 --> 00:28:29,008
Damn it!

417
00:28:29,008 --> 00:28:33,058
Hey Shimizu, what are you so angry about?!
If it's about yesterday, I'm here to apol--

418
00:28:36,518 --> 00:28:39,148
Sorry, I did end up peeping...

419
00:28:43,028 --> 00:28:44,658
I'm not really angry.

420
00:28:46,008 --> 00:28:48,578
I know you didn't mean any harm...

421
00:28:49,158 --> 00:28:52,338
I'd say you were probably late because
of some baseball-related business.

422
00:28:53,298 --> 00:28:58,498
That's why I'm not particularly angry that you were late
or that we didn't get to go to the concert together.

423
00:28:59,878 --> 00:29:00,918
It's just <i>that</i>...

424
00:29:01,348 --> 00:29:06,548
Because you meant no harm, it just explained how
different our feelings towards each other really are.

425
00:29:07,478 --> 00:29:10,218
And the reason why you couldn't tell me
you'd come even if you were late,

426
00:29:10,688 --> 00:29:14,348
was because you weren't even a little excited about all this.

427
00:29:19,518 --> 00:29:21,358
But I'm fine now.

428
00:29:22,318 --> 00:29:26,528
I don't mind being as we were before; just good
friends who share a joke once in a while.

429
00:29:27,158 --> 00:29:30,328
Even if I can't have it all, I don't want to lose everything.

430
00:29:36,118 --> 00:29:37,538
<i>I didn't see that coming.</i>

431
00:29:37,828 --> 00:29:44,008
<i>Ever since we were kids, Shimizu's always been a baseball
teammate, a friend, even almost family...</i>

432
00:29:44,508 --> 00:29:47,178
<i>But I've never even once thought of her as a woman.</i>

433
00:29:47,508 --> 00:29:48,588
<i>And yet...</i>

434
00:29:52,888 --> 00:29:55,308
<i>She</i> is <i>a woman.</i>

435
00:29:56,603 --> 00:29:57,893
I'm really sorry, Goro!

436
00:29:58,973 --> 00:30:02,353
I know I got your hopes up saying you
would get in if you just applied,

437
00:30:02,353 --> 00:30:06,483
as it turns out, you won't be able to participate in the game
between the young players and the national team.

438
00:30:07,823 --> 00:30:11,533
I-I did recommend you, but the circumstances have changed and...

439
00:30:12,453 --> 00:30:14,913
Well, the truth is that the only players on that team will--

440
00:30:14,913 --> 00:30:15,953
I see.

441
00:30:16,533 --> 00:30:19,873
Well then, there's nothing to be done about it... I understand.

442
00:30:20,623 --> 00:30:22,253
G-Goro?

443
00:30:26,213 --> 00:30:27,423
He's acting strangely.

444
00:30:28,093 --> 00:30:29,053
How so?

445
00:30:29,303 --> 00:30:36,063
Well see, last night when I told Goro he wouldn't be selected
to the young players' team, he just kept his cool...

446
00:30:36,853 --> 00:30:40,643
He couldn't wait to face the Japanese team before that.

447
00:30:40,643 --> 00:30:42,523
At first I thought he'd be furious,

448
00:30:42,853 --> 00:30:45,903
but instead he just said there's nothing he can do about it.

449
00:30:45,903 --> 00:30:50,533
Now that you mention it, today he suddenly
left without eating breakfast this morning.

450
00:30:51,653 --> 00:30:55,113
Hmm, I suppose from time to time he can be relaxed.

451
00:30:55,863 --> 00:30:57,283
Well, I'm off.

452
00:30:57,283 --> 00:30:58,703
Have a safe trip.

453
00:31:06,123 --> 00:31:08,553
<i>What's happening to me?</i>

454
00:31:08,843 --> 00:31:10,893
<i>I couldn't sleep at all last night.</i>

455
00:31:12,013 --> 00:31:15,553
It was because you weren't even a little excited about all this.

456
00:31:16,393 --> 00:31:18,303
<i>That's not it.</i>

457
00:31:18,303 --> 00:31:23,433
<i>It's just that she's always been like a
friend to me and I never imagined...</i>

458
00:31:23,893 --> 00:31:28,363
<i>Something so embarrassing as a formal
date or just going out with her.</i>

459
00:31:29,063 --> 00:31:30,483
No-go-ro!

460
00:31:31,363 --> 00:31:32,533
What the hell--

461
00:31:33,583 --> 00:31:36,033
What are you daydreaming about?

462
00:31:36,033 --> 00:31:37,913
Hey, are you doing well?

463
00:31:37,913 --> 00:31:40,333
Tashiro... Fuji...

464
00:31:40,533 --> 00:31:47,423
Taiga told us you had returned, and that you would
take it easy and work out here for a while.

465
00:31:47,583 --> 00:31:51,713
Uchiyama and Miyazaki said they couldn't skip their classes.

466
00:31:51,713 --> 00:31:54,013
They're not very fun, are they?!

467
00:31:54,013 --> 00:31:57,723
But they really wanted to see you, and pass on a "hello".

468
00:31:57,723 --> 00:31:59,593
Ah, really?

469
00:31:59,593 --> 00:32:01,183
So, how was it?

470
00:32:01,183 --> 00:32:03,563
What's your impression of baseball as
it's played in the game's homeland?

471
00:32:04,603 --> 00:32:08,603
Well, wherever you are, baseball is baseball you know.

472
00:32:08,603 --> 00:32:11,323
But I suppose I have a good feel for it.

473
00:32:12,323 --> 00:32:14,193
That's exactly what I thought you'd say.

474
00:32:14,193 --> 00:32:19,913
After all, you're the guy who thought of defeating Kaido
when there wasn't even a baseball club in Seishuu.

475
00:32:19,913 --> 00:32:21,243
But still...

476
00:32:21,243 --> 00:32:23,753
Who thought that they would still be using this field.

477
00:32:24,293 --> 00:32:28,553
We didn't go to Koshien, but this place
brings back the best memories.

478
00:32:29,833 --> 00:32:33,133
but, we missed our entrance into the university, though.

479
00:32:33,883 --> 00:32:35,513
Don't blame that on baseball!

